HEADWORD: Woolward-going
<hw>Wool"ward-go`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wearing of
woolen clothes next the skin as a matter of penance.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their . . . <qex>woolward-going</qex>, and rising at midnight.</q>
<rj><qau>Tyndale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woon</ent>⟦br⟧
